𝐑𝐢𝐬𝐤 𝐅𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐨𝐫𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐒𝐈𝐃𝐒:
▪️Prone sleep position
▫️Sleeping on a soft surface
▪️Co-sleeping or bed sharing (including co-bedding of twins)
▫️Maternal smoking during pregnancy
▪️Second hand smoke exposure
▫️Overheating
▪️Limited-to-no prenatal care
▫️Young maternal age or advanced maternal age
▪️Preterm birth and/or low birth weight
▫️Toys, loose bedding, other objects and pillows in the crib
▪️Formula-fed infant
▫️Male gender of the infant
▪️African American, American Indian, or Alaskan Native

𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐝 𝐒𝐚𝐟𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐒𝐥𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐏𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐑𝐞𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐞 𝐒𝐈𝐃𝐒:
🛏Bed should be flat + mattress should be firm
🚼Place infant on his/her back to sleep (tummy time only when awake & supervised)
🧸Keep soft objects, stuffed animals, loose bedding, blankets, pillows, etc. OUT of the crib
🚫Do not use crib bumpers
🤱🏻Infant should NOT be swaddled in his sleep area
🚬Do not smoke or let anyone smoke around your baby
🛌Baby should sleep alone in his own crib";}i:56;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:57;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:4;}i:58;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEvF7-nhOvg";}i:59;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:249:"https://scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118708065_636370090342782_8957447887539107408_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=106&_nc_ohc=zdKVxd65-agAX98VCzy&oh=9117a0cdf3b3a8fc9a8efe3328bb6164&oe=5F7CBA58";}i:60;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:61;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:30130855378;}i:62;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:63;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:64;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:65;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391155965816197351";}i:66;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEvF66ZB9Dn";}i:67;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599268025;}i:68;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:437:"Sending you happy weekend vibes!

