👉🏼 It is a known fact that breast milk provides immunological protection against many illnesses & is the best source of nutrition for most infants #breastisbest. Most often, babies who are nursed remain healthy even when their mothers fall ill with an infectious disease. 🤒 This is because mothers produce specific antibodies & many other critical immune factors in their milk to protect their infants + enhance their immune responses. 🧬 These immunologic factors aid the infants’ bodies to respond more effectively to exposure + help them to fight infection. 🦠🥊 

Much is still unknown about COVID-19. However, what we do know is that mother-to-fetus transmission during pregnancy is unlikely, but after birth, a newborn is susceptible to direct person-to-person spread. ✨𝐂𝐮𝐫𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐞𝐯𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞-𝐛𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐮𝐩𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐬 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐛𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐤 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐛𝐚𝐛𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐧 𝐢𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐲 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐢𝐧𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐂𝐎𝐕𝐈𝐃-𝟏𝟗.✨

